SIMPLE: muzzle
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Muzzle
<hw>Muz"zle</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE. <ets>mosel</ets>,
OF. <ets>musel</ets>, F. <ets>museau</ets> muzzle or snout, LL.
<ets>musellus</ets>, fr. <ets>musus</ets>, <ets>morsus</ets>. See
<er>Muse</er>, <pos>v. i.</pos>, and cf. <er>Morsel</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>The projecting mouth and nose of a quadruped, as of a
horse; a snout.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The mouth of a thing; the end for entrance or
discharge; <as>as, the <ex>muzzle</ex> of a gun</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A fastening or covering (as a band or cage) for the
mouth of an animal, to prevent eating or vicious biting.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>With golden <qex>muzzles</qex> all their mouths were bound</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Muzzle sight</b></col>. <fld>(Gun.)</fld> <cd>See
<er>Dispart</er>, <pos>n.</pos>, 2.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Muzzle</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Muzzle
<hw>Muz"zle</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Muzzled</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Muzzling</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <ety>[F.
<ets>museler</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To bind the mouth of; to
fasten the mouth of, so as to prevent biting or eating; hence,
figuratively, to bind; to sheathe; to restrain from speech or action;
<as>as, the dictator <ex>muzzled</ex> all the newspapers</as>.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧My dagger <xex>muzzled</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Thou shalt not <qex>muzzle</qex> the ox when he treadeth out the
corn.</q> <rj><qau>Deut. xxv. 4.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To fondle with the closed mouth.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>L'Estrange.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Muzzle</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Muzzle
<hw>Muz"zle</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To bring the mouth or muzzle
near.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The bear <qex>muzzles</qex> and smells to him.</q>
<rj><qau>L'Estrange.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Muzzle-loader</ent>⟦br⟧
